<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<activity wordnetid="100407535" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../105/4932105.xml">
Faraday School kidnapping</link></activity>
</psychological_feature>
</act>
</juvenile>
</causal_agent>
</wrongdoing>
</crime>
</event>
</transgression>
</person>
</child>
</physical_entity>
, in a starring role opposite <manufacturer wordnetid="110292316" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../613/381613.xml">
Rachel Ward</link></actor>
</manufacturer>
. Wells appeared as a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../515/254515.xml">
villain</link> in <it><link>
Last Man Standing</link></it> (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../670/34670.xml">
1988</link>).</p>

</ss1>
<ss1>
<st>
1990s and 2000s</st>
<p>

In 1992, Wells appeared in one of the few roles in which he is not cast as a villain, in the short-lived 1992 television comedy series <it><beginning wordnetid="100235435" confidence="0.8">
<change wordnetid="100191142" confidence="0.8">
<show wordnetid="100520257" confidence="0.8">
<entertainment wordnetid="100429048" confidence="0.8">
<ending wordnetid="106308765" confidence="0.8">
<morpheme wordnetid="106306233" confidence="0.8">
<change_of_state wordnetid="100199130" confidence="0.8">
